OHHHH! That was very, very close! What a delivery to begin with. Also, big turn for Lyon there. He lands this outside off, it pitches and turns back in sharply. Root covers his off stump and leaves it. The ball just about misses the front pad and the off pole.
A halt in play! Tim Paine has asked for his helmet but it is taking long to come.
Double change! Nathan Lyon comes on too.
Another delivery on a length and around off, this is blocked out. A good start by Siddle.
Almost! Siddle gets this one to come back in from outside off, Burns looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads. A muted appeal from the bowler but nothing from the umpire.
Another one on a length and around off, Burns lunges and keeps it out.
Good length and on off, this is defended. This is what you will get from Siddle, he will constantly hit one length.
Fuller and on off, Burns pushes it to mid off.

Siddle finds the edge on the first ball itself but it goes down towards third man for two. He comes from around the wicket and lands it on off, it straightens. Burns looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge.
Peter Siddle is on! First change for Australia.
Full and outside off, Joe looks to drive but the ball comes in a touch and goes off the inner half towards mid on.
Outside off, dabbed straight to gully.
Smart from Burns. Gets a short ball, outside off and taps it towards point for a quick single.
Paine is on the aggressive here. Gets in Travis Head at short leg, indicating there would be no let-up in terms of the short stuff.
We are in for a delay. There is the mandatory concussion check and Aleem Dar is concerned. Burns looks okay though. Here comes the physio. Nothing much. Just a calm question check and we are ready.

FOUR LEG BYES! On the helmet! The first one to hit the head gear this series. A bouncer from Cummins, outside off, Rory ducks but it is not the proper technique. He is half-standing, half-ducking and the ball shoots in, taking the helmet and flying over Tim Paine to the fine leg fence.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.
On a length outside off, Burns looks to defend but the ball comes in late and  beats him.
First ball Pattinson bowls to a left-hander today, he fails to adjust. He bowls it on the pads. Burns looks to flick but misses. It hits the pads and rolls on the leg side. A leg bye taken.
A single! This is on middle, Root guides it towards point and takes one.

Just short! Root did not get it right off the middle and that probably saved him. This is fuller on off, Root looks to drive it straight down the ground. He though ends up mistiming it back towards the bowler but it falls short.
This is outside off, Root need not play at those.
Root is off the mark! Not in convincing manner though. This is on middle, Root ends up playing outside the line this time, it goes off the inner half through square leg for a couple.

This is lovely, lovely stuff! Every ball he is bowling, it seems like he would take a wicket. He goes wide of the crease and angles this one into the off pole. It pitches and straightens. Root plays the original trajectory and the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
An ambitious appeal! This is angled into the pads, Burns looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads. Cummins appeals but it is going over. Hawk Eye confirms the same.
BEATEN! Good delivery this! He comes around the wicket and angles it into off. It is shorter in length. Burns goes back and tries to defend but the outside edge is beaten as the ball straightens.
A back of a length ball this time, Burns works it to mid-wicket.
Shorter and on off, Burns plays it well as he hops and defends it onto the ground.

A little too straight on middle, Burns works it to mid-wicket. Maybe the end here is not supporting Cummins as we saw Pattinson get good movement but Pat not getting a lot. However, he is more of a hit-the-deck bowler.
Back of a length on off, Burns blocks it. Cummins too has to support James here. If he gets into his own, he could be deadly.
First poor ball by him today. Down the leg side, Root looks to flick but misses. A successful over comes to an end by Pattinson.
Well bowled again! This is outside off, Root looks to play at it but then pulls out. James is really bowling well here, it is a delight to watch him at the moment.
Goes fuller and on middle, Root strokes it to mid on. Good shot that.
Outside off, left alone. Not a good ball to bowl to the new batter.
Joe Root is the new man in.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Pattinson draws first blood and he deserves this wicket. He has been excellent today morning and he gets his reward. Also, he has troubled Roy throughout and this was probably on the cards. Another lovely delivery by Pattinson. It pitches on off and it is on a length. It takes off after pitching. Roy is drawn into the stroke. He tries to drop his hands at the end but the ball kisses the outside edge and goes low to Smith at second slip. He takes a good catch. James is pumped up and Australia get rid of the dangerous Roy early. England trail by 262.
In the fifth stump channel. Roy moves across and then lets it be.
4 slips in place now! No gully though.
Third leave in a row as Cummins bowls another one outside off. A good comeback by Cummins after the first ball but he still does not seem to be at his best today morning.
Well bowled! In the corridor of uncertainty. Burns shoulders arms to this one.
Just behind a driving length around off, angling away. Burns lets it be.
A little too straight again by Cummins, Burns pushes it to mid on.
Corrects his line and length this time. It is shorter and on off, Burns keeps it out.
FOUR! Easy-peasy! Cummins changes the angle but bowls it on the pads. Burns loves it there, he flicks it through square leg and the ball races away to the fence.
In the previous over, the camera showed us Jimmy Anderson doing a morning jog, which is good news for England. They missed him badly in the first innings and would want him around in the second dig.
A good nut to end a good over! This is slightly fuller around off, comes back in. Roy looks to play it against the movement but it goes off the inner half to mid on.
Gets this one to come back in after pitching it around middle, the length is a touch shorter though. Roy looks to play at it but misses to get hit high on the pads.

Played that with soft hands and hence the ball does not carry! Pattinson is troubling Roy here. He lands it around off and gets it to straighten. Roy looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge but falls short of Smith at second slip. He makes a good stop in the end diving to his left.
Slightly outside off, hoping Roy plays a loose shot. Jason does not get tempted and he lets it be.

A couple of overs too late, here comes the fourth slip. Australia might be looking towards Paine to be more active, rather than reactive. For someone like Jason Roy, who likes to go hard at the ball, always protecting the slip cordon is a must. Because once he gets his eye in, he will send the bowlers out on a leather hunt.
Continues bowling it on a length and on middle, Roy pushes it to mid on.
Another good delivery by Pattinson! It is on off and on a length. Roy shows the full face of the bat and pushes it to mid off.
Shorter and angled into the batter, Burns pushes it to mid on. He has looked at ease against Cummins till now.
On the fuller side again, once again there is no movement for Cummins. Burns strokes it to mid on.
Outside off, Burns does not fiddle with it.
Another ball on a length and around off, this is blocked nicely. Burns has looked nice and good till now.
Good comeback! This is angled into the off pole, it lands on a length and straightens. Burns defends inside the line and gets beaten.
FOUR! Second boundary of the day, this time it is Burns who hits it. Cummins goes full and outside off, Burns drives it square on the off side and bags a boundary.
A dot to end a good over by Pattinson. Back of a length on off, Roy stands tall and keeps it out.
Shorter in length and on off, Roy stands tall and defends it out.
This one stays low! It pitches on off and skids through. Roy gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
Good delivery! Shortens his length around off and it shapes away. Roy plays it well though. He initially is drawn into the stroke but then bails out seeing the swing.

EDGY FOUR! Had there been a 4th slip, Australia would have got their first wicket. Lucky boundary for Roy there. First runs today and it is in a fortunate manner. Pattinson goes full and around off, it shapes away later. Roy looks to go hard at it but the ball flies off the outside edge and past third slip, to the third man fence. Maybe the fielder could have put in a dive there but he was late to react I feel.
Starts off with a loosener outside off, Roy shoulders arms to this one.
James Pattinson to bowl from the other end.
A maiden to begin but not a threatening one! The last ball is outside off, Burns makes an easy leave.
A good nut this one! It is on off and around a length. Burns defends it nicely.
Another very full ball, this is almost a yorker. Burns jams it out to the man at mid off.
This one is angled into the batter, Burns works it to the man at mid-wicket.
Swing this time! The line though is outside off, it swings away further. Burns shoulders arms to this one.
Cummins steams in from around the wicket and bowls this full around off, no swing on offer for him. Burns is a touch late in his drive and mistimes it on the off side.

We are all set for the action to begin! It ain't very cloudy but it is not sunny too. The English openers, Jason Roy and Rory Burns make their way out to resume their innings. Pat Cummins will start the proceedings for Australia. Three slips and a gully in place. Here we go...

How do England look at this pitch? How do supporters look at this track? When the visitors were crumbling at 122/8, it looked like there is plenty on the pitch for the seamers. But then, looking at the way Siddle and Lyon played, it gives plenty of confidence to the hosts' batsmen. What exactly is there in the pitch then? Actually, not much. It was swing which got the better of OZ and they would need exactly that to stop England. Overcast conditions did not help them either. Conditions today are bright and sunny, so that could mean extra work for the Aussie bowlers.

Right. That was all about Steve Smith. But this game is not ONLY about Smithy, is it? There were other players too who played a role in a fantastic opening day. First, it was Broad, who ran through the fragile Aussie batting line-up, to finish with a 5-for and get into the list of bowlers with 100 Ashes wickets. Then, there was Woakes, who just strut his stuff with the Dukes ball. But the man who was missed the most. His 4 overs were the only output for England and his absence, can be argued, allowed the Aussies to recover.

Down and out in the dumps. Bring out the sandpaper! Boo Smith! One of the culprits, Warner, dislodged cheaply despite a reprieve. Another culprit, Bancroft, not lasting long either. How long will Steve Smith last? Ask again. How long will Steve Smith last? Long. Very long. Lasting till the very last ball of the innings. On a day when nothing much seemed to go right for Australia, this man stuck his guts out like wet sand sticks onto dry paper, making the Barmy Army eat humble pie. A day which saw the Aussies tottering at 122/8, ended with OZ finishing with 284. Of which, the former skipper scored JUST 144. Yes, just. What a way to begin the opening day of the 2019 Ashes. We now welcome you to the second day of the first Test between England and Australia at Edgbaston.
... DAY 2, SESSION 1 ...

Australia will aim to do what England did come Friday morning. But how will the conditions be? Good for batting or bowling? Join us at 11 am local (1000 GMT) for all the action from Day 2. ADIOS! TAKE CARE!

From 122/8 to 284 all out! The talk of the town will be Steve Smith for scoring more than 50 percent of the team total. But do not forget a certain Stuart Broad who etched his name into record books with his 100th Ashes wicket.

That ends a fabulous opening day of the Ashes. Down and out, a team fights back. Now, we await to see how the other will respond come Friday. England have done well to see off the 2 overs of play and will aim to get a good partnership going on Day 2.

Roy survives and England will head into Day 2 unharmed. Fuller on off, it comes in. Roy looks to defend but the ball goes towards square leg off the inner half of his bat. They come back for the second as the fielder from fine leg cleans it up. STUMPS ON DAY 1!
This one nips in too. Roy this time defends it but not in a traditional fashion.
Good comeback from Pattinson. Steams in and bowls an incoming pacy ball on a length. Roy looks to defend but misses and the cherry hits his abdomen.
FOUR! Roy is off the mark! Scores the first boundary of England's innings. Overpitched on off, Roy shows his white-ball form and creams his drive through covers for a boundary.
Fuller on middle, Burns turns it to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Starts with a good length ball outside off. There is late away swing on it, Burns shoulders arms to this ball.
We will have one more over here before Stumps. It will be the returning, James Pattinson who will bowl the last over of the day.
Full on off, Roy gets his composure back and defends it off the front foot.
Play and a miss! Roy looks to go for glory. It is a short ball outside off and Roy goes for a big pull, an unnecessary shot at this stage. Luckily for Roy he does not edge it.
Good length ball on off, it nips in. Roy glances it towards mid-wicket off the inner half of his bat.
A solid, confident front foot defense from Roy to start his innings. Full on off, Roy defends it with a straight bat.
Burns and England are off the mark! Full ball which comes in with the angle. Burns flicks it with the swing through mid-wicket. The fielder cleans it up before the ropes as the batsmen take three.
Starts with a fuller ball with very little movement on off, Burns defends it off the front foot.

Now then, England have 7 overs to play out today. It is a very tricky period. They would be hopeful of not losing a wicket. Australia on the other hand, will want a wicket at least. Will England send out a nightwatchman? They did that the last time against Ireland and that man went onto score something in the 90s. That player though is not playing today. We will have to wait to find out who comes out to bat. Stay tuned.

A very tiring day for the English bowlers. They dearly missed James Anderson out there. Their bowlers looked flat today and just did not look threatening. Stokes was probably the pick of the bowlers for them as he finished with a three-fer. His wickets though came very late as the batters till then, had done their job.

What a batting performance from Australia! They have almost batted the whole day and have probably batted England out of the game. They entered the day slightly on the back foot but Head and Smith's partnership took them ahead. Smith and Wade then continued the good work done by the partnership before. Both scored tons. Cummins and Pattinson then added the finishing touches as they smashed the bowlers to all parts of the ground and the 78-run stand has given England a huge task ahead.
SIX! High and handsome! A leg spinner on middle, Pattinson lofts it over the long on fence and it goes all the way. Paine is seen calling them back. AUSTRALIA HAVE DECLARED! Target for England, 398!
The declaration now might be close as Siddle was seen removing his pads.

DROPPED! A difficult one but England need to take each chance that comes their way. Cummins again clears his front leg trying to hit this one down the ground. He does so uppishly and Denly throws his right arm at it. He gets a hand to it and stops three runs as the ball loops over Denly's head after hitting his head and the batters take a single.
The batsman charges down the wicket. One run added to the total.
Denly bowls a loopy one on leg. Cummins again swings this time, he connects but finds the man at mid-wicket.

FOUR! Smashed and smashed hard down the ground! Cummins is becoming the aggressor now and after hitting it to the boundary looks towards the dressing room. This one is flat and full on off pole, Cummins clears his front leg out of the way and powerfully lofts it over the bowlers head.
FOUR! Up and over! Denly floats it outside off, Cummins drags it against the turn over the mid on fielder for a boundary.
A low full toss on the pads, this is worked to the man at mid-wicket.
Another short ball on middle, Cummins pulls it through mid-wicket and takes one.
Very full outside off, Pattinson jams it out through covers for one.
From around the wicket, Broad bowls it full and on the pads, Cummins looks to flick but misses. The ball hits the pads and rolls towards fine leg. A leg bye taken.
Once again clears his front leg. Broad goes full and outside off, Pattinson jams it down towards third man for one.

SIX! Take that, says Pattinson. What a shot that is! Third maximum for him. He clears his front leg and Broad lands it on a length and around leg. Pattinson tonks it over the long on fence for a biggie.

This time flat and short just outside off by Denly, Cummins opens the face of his bat and guides it towards the third man region to take a couple. This also brings up the 50-run stand between Cummins and Pattinson in just 62 balls. England have struggled throughout the day and this partnership only goes on to emphasize how much. Pattinson and Cummins have frustrated the bowling attack and also kept on scoring runs at a very good rate. The only question that now remains is when will Australia decide to declare this innings.
Full and floated on middle by Denly, Cummins plays this through mid on. The fielders give it a chase and collect it as the batters take two.
Denly bowls this one fuller and on off. JP sweeps this one towards square leg and takes a single.
This time JP goes for the reverse sweep to this full ball on off, but again he misses.
Shortish and on the off side for Pattinson, he tries to cut but misses.
Tossed up full and on off, Cummins plays it towards point for a single.
Down the leg side, JP throws his bat at it but misses.
Pattinson makes room and Broad follows him. Pattinson swings but misses to get hit on the pads.
A bumper on middle, Pattinson ducks under it.
Back of a length on middle, Pattinson keeps it out.

Another drop! Difficult catch again. Rory Burns is the man one more time. This is short and angling away from Cummins. He looks to upper cut it. Rory at third man runs in, dives forward, he gets two hands to it but fails to hang on. A single taken.
A good short one on middle, Pattinson looks to pull but mistimes it towards square leg for one.
Way outside off, Cummins lets that one be.
Pattinson plays this one off the front foot towards point and takes a single.

DROPPED! Tough to call it that though, it was an exceptional effort. This is floated up on off, Cummins looks to go inside out but does not get under the delivery. He hits it uppishly but low to the right of Burns at covers. Rory dives to his right and stretches one hand out but fails to hang on. It rolls towards mid off. A single taken.
Shortish ball on off played to point. This single also brings up the 350-run lead for England.

Four Byes! Ooh! How did that miss everything? Again flat on off, the ball turns and maybe too much. Pattinson tries to sweep but misses and the ball is also missed by Bairstow. It goes to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Flat on off pole, James goes for the reverse sweep but misses as the ball hits his pads.
Tim Paine has still not changed into his whites so declaration does not seem to be coming anytime soon.
Joe Denly is back into the attack.
A short one outside off, Cummins lets it be.
On the shorter side, the batter works it to the man at mid-wicket.
A single now as this ball on the pads is flicked to the man at fine leg.
Now then some issue with the ball. It seems to have got wet as it might have fell in a glass of beer. It is being changed.

SIX! He has picked the bones out of that one! Pattinson makes room and Broad follows him with a short one. James smashes it over the square leg fence for a biggie. The lead is above 350. Not sure how many more do Australia want.
A bumper on middle, the batsman ducks under it.
Goes short from around the wicket. Cummins works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Pattinson again comes onto the front foot and blocks it out.
Pattinson blocks this off the front foot towards Ali.

No ball! Woah! What was this by Ali? He goes to float this one but maybe he does too much. The ball goes straight into the keepers hand as Pattinson tries to slash at it but misses. Umpire gives a warning to Ali for the beamer.
Floated outside off, by Ali, Pattinson gets a leading edge and the ball rolls to point.
Fullish ball floated on middle and off, Pattinson plays it back to Ali.
SIX! That is right off the middle. The lead is now 346. Pattinson plays the slog sweep. He hits it extremely well and it clears the mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Shorter and outside off, Pattinson looks to cut but misses.
Drinks!
Length ball on the off side, Cummins plays this towards point.
Short ball again to Pattinson, he pulls this one towards mid on for one.
Short ball again to Cummins, he pulls this one towards square leg for a single.

Short of a length ball pitched outside leg, Cummins tries to play the upper cut but misses. The England team appeal in a low voice but the umpire shakes his head. The replays roll in and the Ultra Edge shows a spike. However, no reviews left for the English side. They too did not seem confident with their appeal so the edge might have been a very faint one.
Shorter in length and on off, Cummins stands tall and keeps it out.
Back of a length on off, Cummins guides it nicely through point and takes two.
Stuart Broad is back on.
Short and flat on off, James cuts it to the point fielder.
Length ball on the off side, Pattinson leaves it.
FOUR! Swept and swept well by James. Ali floats it on a good length on off, James goes down on one knee and sweeps this one towards deep square leg. The ball races away to the fence.
Full length ball on the pads. Pushed back towards the bowler.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full length ball tossed up on off, played towards mid on for a single.
On the leg side, it hits the pads of JP and the ball carries to Bairstow.
Good length ball on the off side, Cummins pushes this one through cover point for a single.
Short of a length ball on the off side, Cummins plays it towards point.
Fuller on the legs of James, he plays it towards fine leg for a single.

FOUR! Woah! What great timing here by James Pattinson! This is a length ball just outside off, Pattinson slightly goes onto the back foot and cuts it towards backward point. The ball slowly trudges towards the fence for a boundary.
Short ball on middle, the ball drifts towards the leg side. Pattinson ducks under it and lets it go.
Cummins says, enough of blocking. He goes for the slog sweep but does not time it at all. It goes off the inner half to mid-wicket.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floats it up outside off, Cummins looks to defend but the ball turns back in and hits the pad. A muted appeal from the bowler but that is doing too much.
Gives it a lot of air on off, Cummins hits it to the man at mid off.
Floats it up on off, Cummins keeps it out.
Flighted ball on off, Cummins looks to drive it against the turn through the off side but it goes off the inner half back to the bowler.
Pattinson tries to play at this length ball outside off but misses it completely.
Fuller ball on middle and leg, worked towards mid on.

Oohh! Close call here for Cummins but he survives. Stokes bowls this one on the hips of Cummins, he tries to dab it towards the leg side but does so uppishly and in some pace. The ball goes to the right of Jos Buttler at short leg but he ducks to save himself. Difficult chance but a chance nonetheless. The ball rolls towards deep square leg for a single.
Good length ball on middle and off, Cummins plays it back to the bowler.
Short ball on middle, Cummins ducks under it.
Wide outside off, the ball is half-stopped by the man at point, substitute fielder Sam Curran. The batters take three.
On the leg pole, Pattinson looks to defend but it goes off the inner half down towards fine leg for one.
Off the mark straightaway! This is a very full ball on off, Cummins strokes it down to long off for one.
Pat Cummins is the new man in.

OUT! BOWLED! Two wickets in quick succession for England. Paine is walking back now after getting off to a start. This is an absolute beauty from Moeen Ali. An off spinner's dream delivery. He gives it a lot of loop and lands it outside off. The ball pitches and turns back in sharply. Paine looks to defend but the ball sneaks through the gap between bat and pad and hits the off pole. The last recognized batter is out of here. Still no declaration though. Australia lead by 319.
Flatter and on middle, Pattinson works it towards mid on for one. The fielder did score a direct hit at the non-striker's end but the batter is well in.
On the off pole, this is defended.
Flatter and on off, Paine pushes it through covers for one.
This is angled into the batter, JP works it to mid-wicket.
A yorker on middle, Pattinson gets his bat down in time and keeps it out.
A bumper on middle, Pattinson ducks under it.
Outside off, Pattinson lets it be.
James Pattinson replaces Wade out in the middle.

OUT! Straight to the man! Wade is out of here but he walks back after doing an excellent job. He would feel hard done by as he had really hit that well. A short ball on the body, Wade pulls it right off the middle. He though does not keep it down and also does not get the desired distance. Denly at deep backward square leg takes it easily. Wade too receives a standing ovation as he walks off. Australia lead by 317. How many more will they want as there are no signs of them declaring.
Shorter in length and around off, Wade guides it gully.

NOT OUT! Missing the off pole, it has not turned back in enough. England lose both their reviews now. This is outside off, it turns back in. Paine gets his pad outside the line of off pole and makes a leave. It hits the front pad. An appeal follows but the umpire shakes his head. JB wants it to be reviewed and Root does so. Replays roll in and they show that ball is missing the off pole.
Review time! Paine has not offered a shot and is hit on the pads. Bairstow feels it is close. Let's see if the ball is turning back in enough.
Now the paddle sweep, hits it well through short fine leg and a couple taken. Paine too wants to score quickly.
FOUR! Clever shot! Knows there was nobody behind point on the off side. Brings the reverse sweep out and hits it through that region for a boundary.
Floats it up on off, Paine lunges and keeps it out.
Shorter and outside off, this is slapped through covers for one.
Good fielding! The captain leading by example! This is a full toss on middle, Wade hits it towards mid on where Root dives to his right and stops it.
Moeen Ali is back into the attack!
Back of a length and on off, Paine defends it out.
Another good short one outside off, Paine once again lets it be.
Shorter in length and on middle, Paine stands tall and keeps it out.
A good short one on middle, Paine evades it.

In the air... but safe! Lucky there was Paine. A short ball on the body. Paine initially looks to pull but then tries to move away by taking the eyes off. The ball hits the glove and lobs on the off side. Actually Paine was not lucky there as it was off the shoulder.
Bowls a short delivery outside leg, Paine does not bother to play at that.
A single to end as Paine works it through square leg. 400 up for Australia.
Flatter and around off, Wade stays leg side of the ball and pushes it through covers for one. This is now Wade's highest Test score.
FOUR! Wade is hitting boundaries at will at the moment. He is oozing in confidence. Very full and on off, Wade strokes it past the mid off fielder and the ball races away to the fence.
A single as this is flicked through mid-wicket.
Down the leg side, it is padded away.
Leg spinner on leg stump, it is shorter in length. Paine comes down the track and looks to flick but misses to get hit on the arm.
Goes short again, this time Wade evades it.

OUCH! That might have hurt! Stokes bangs it short and it keeps climbing on the batter. Wade tries to defend by taking one hand off the handle. The ball misses the bat and hits the arm of the batsman. Wade shows no pain. Hostile stuff from Stokes.

FOUR! Top edge and a boundary! Lead above 300, one believes, England are probably batted out of the game. Also runs are coming at a very good pace here. This is short and down the leg side. Wade helps it on its way to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Back of a length on off, Wade defends it onto the ground.
On the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Up and over for a couple! Stokes goes short and wide outside off again, Paine guides it over point. Third man gets across and keeps it down to two.
Floats it outside off, Wade strokes it to covers.
On middle, this is kept out.

FOUR! 100 for Matthew Wade! His third in Tests and what a return for him after almost 2 years out of the national side! Just a single in the first innings and a ton to follow it up. Brilliant. There was a time when there were doubts about him playing Test cricket again, he gets an opportunity here and scores a ton. He gets there in style. Brings out the reverse sweep and hits it through short third man. It means a lot to him as his celebration indicates. He gets a bear hug from his skipper.
On the pads agian, Paine works it through square leg and takes one.
On the pads, Paine pads it away.
Fuller outside off, Wade strokes it crisply through covers and a run is taken. 50-run stand up between the two. Another handy stand.
On a good length on off, Paine blocks it off the back foot.
Short of a length delivery, Wade pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Good length delivery on middle, Wade defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nice shot. Matthew Wade is just six away from his century. Short and outside off, Wade cuts it hard through point for a boundary.
On a length and outside off, Paine guides it towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
Length delivery on middle, Paine plays it towards mid on for a run.
On middle, kept out.
On middle, this is kept out.
Wade looks to play the revervse sweep but misses as the ball outside bounces a touch more.
On the pads, Paine looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. It rolls on the leg side for one.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Nice shot for one! Floats it up on off, Wade strokes it through covers for one.
Length delivery on middle, Paine flicks it to mid-wicket. 11 from the over.
On a good length on off, Paine defends it out.
FOUR! Nice shot. Full on middle, Paine drives it through mid on for a boundary.
SIX! Excellent shot. Short and outside off, Paine cuts it over point for a maximum. Tim Paine goes past 1000 Test runs.
NO BALL! Stokes oversteps! On a good length on off, Paine keeps it out.
Good length delivery on middle, Paine defends it off the back foot.
On a good length and outside off, Paine taps it to point.
Ben Stokes to bowl from the other end.
Paine was a goner! He works this to the man at mid on and takes off. Roy gets to the ball quickly and has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses. Paine had already given up.
On off, Wade defends outside the line, it goes off the inner half through mid-wicket for one.
Flatter and on middle, Wade defends it out.
Comes down the track and takes it on the full, works it through mid-wicket for one.
On the off pole again, this one keeps low. Paine defends it off the toe-end.
Fuller and on middle, it is hit back towards the bowler.
We are back for the final session on Day 4. Matthew Wade and Tim Paine to resume their innings. The English players walk out to the middle. Skipper Root to start the proceedings for England.
... DAY 4, SESSION 3 ...

The lead is 266 at the moment and one feels if Australia do well in the last session, they will probably bat England out of the game. England need to come out strong and pick the remaining wickets as quickly as possible. Do join us for the final session in a while.

Another session which has belonged to the visitors! Yes, they did lose Steve Smith but not before the champion played his part. The session started with Wade and Smith scoring runs at will. The two added another 100-run stand which saw the lead go past 200. The England bowlers looked flat and it seemed we would be in for a wicket-less session. However, the new ball changed that as Woakes got rid of Smith. Wade and Paine though have started their partnership in a positive manner and have already added 25 in 23 balls.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Full on leg, Wade flicks it through square leg for a boundary. THAT IS TEA ON DAY 4!
Short of a length delivery on middle, Paine pulls it through mid-wicket for a run.
Outside off, Paine leaves it alone.
Full on leg, Wade flicks it hard through square leg. The batsmen take a single.
Length delivery on middle, Paine flicks it towards square leg. The batsmen cross ends.
Good length delivery on off, Paine defends it off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Wade defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Nice shot! Full on middle, Wade times it beautifully through mid on for a boundary. Moeen Ali chases the ball but has no chance.
Full on off, Wade drives it to mid off.
Good length delivery on middle, Wade blocks it off the back foot.
On a length on off, Wade looks to drive but gets it of the inner half of the bat. It goes towards square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
On a good length and outside off, Wade shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Paine defends it out.
On a good length on middle, Paine blocks it off the back foot.
Full and outside off, Wade drives it through point. The batsmen cross ends.
WIDE! Bowls it wide outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
Broad bowls it full on middle, Wade flicks it to mid-wicket.
Play and a miss! On a good length and outside off, Wade looks to drive but misses it.
FOUR! Terrific shot. Full and outside off, Wade drives it beautifully through covers for a boundary. Nobody moved there.
Well fielded! Fuller and on off, Wade strokes it wide of mid off. Broad there dives to his right and saves three for his side. End of a successful over for England.
Back of a length on off, this is kept out.
A single now as this is worked down to deep backward square leg.
Another couple! Good shot this. On a good length around off, Paine strokes it through covers for two.
Paine is off the mark! Woakes bowls it fuller and it tails back in. Paine works it through mid-wicket for two.
Skipper Tim Paine is the new man in.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Stop the press, Steve Smith has been dismissed. The second new ball works wonders for England. Once again a wicket out of nowhere. A much, much-needed one as the two were taking the game away from them. Australia still on top but England now will feel they are right back in this. This wicket will inject a lot of positivity into them. Woakes bowls this fuller and outside off, it swings away further. Smith goes after it but due to the movement, the ball goes off the outside edge and Bairstow takes it with a dive to his right. Maybe a lapse in concentration for Smith as he was generally leaving such deliveries. Nevertheless, end of a magical innings by Smith. He walks off to a standing ovation and he deserves every bit of it. It is because of him, Australia are in the position they are. For England though, is this the opening they needed? It has to be if they are to actually get back into the game.
WIDE! Woakes too starts with a loosener! Full and way too wide outside off. It swings away further. Smith lets it be. Bairstow dives to his right and makes a half-stop but no runs conceded.
Chris Woakes is back into the attack.
A good shot to end a very good first over with the second new ball by Broad. Fuller and on off, Wade strokes it to covers.
On a good length outside off, Wade shoulders arms to it.
Edged but short! This is on off, it straightens a touch. Wade looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge but lands short of second slip.
Around off, Wade defends it.

NOT OUT! Height does save him. Excellent review by Wade. That did not look out to be honest. It was shorter in length and it is angled into the batter. Wade looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads. A huge shout and the umpire raises the finger. Wade reviews. Replays show that the ball is going over the leg pole.
Have England finally got another? Wade has been adjudged LBW but he has reviewed. Height can save him.
A loosener to begin with! It is on the pads, Smith works it through square leg for one.
The second new ball has finally been taken by England! Broad comes onto bowl now. Can the change in ball produce the magic for England? They will dearly hope so.
Shorter and wide outside off, Smith slaps it through covers for one.
On middle, defended.
Very full on leg stump, Smith works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Faint touch! This is on the pads, Smith goes back and works it fine down the leg side. He moves to 140.
On the pads, it is flicked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Easy-peasy for Australia at the moment. The last ball is whipped down to long on for one. The stand between the two is 119 now and the lead is 234.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads. The batsmen have run through for a single.
FOUR! That has been nailed! Slightly short and Wade pounces onto it. He goes back quickly and pulls it over the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
Floated delivery on middle, Smith flicks it towards leg side for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Wade makes room and slaps it through covers. The batsmen cross ends.
Tossed up outside off, Smith drives it through point for a single.
Outside off, the batter lets it be. End of an over where Smith could have been dismissed but he is still batting out there.
Edged but short! Shorter and outside off, Wade looks to cut but due to the extra bounce, it goes off the outside edge but lands short of short third man.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Floats it up on off, Wade strokes it to covers.

Direct hit and Smith was a goner! Excellent fielding! Shorter and around off, Wade cuts it through point. They take one and go for the second. Denly gets to the ball in the deep and then has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Smith was well short. Actually replays show, had Joe Root been behind the stumps, collected the ball and whipped the bails off, Smith would have still been short. Root though would have felt it was an easy double and hence, he was standing in front of the stumps and in the end, he failed to collect the throw. Another opportunity goes abegging. England can't afford this, especially now.
Floats it up on the pads, Smith works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Good running! It is the straighter one on off, Smith drops it on the off side and takes off. Stokes from first slip goes after it and has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
A little too full this time, Wade manages to hit it through covers for one.
On middle, Wade defends it nicely.
Tosses it up on off, the batter strokes it to covers.
Very full on middle, Wade jams it back to the bowler.
Floats it up on off, Wade defends it onto the ground.
The second new ball is now available! Not taken as of now though.
A single to end the over! Flatter and on off, Wade pushes it through covers for one.
The quicker one and on the stumps, Wade goes back and keeps it out.
This is way too wide outside off, Wade lets it be.
BEATEN! Root is really bowling well here. He bowls this flatter and around off, Wade looks to push at it but the ball turns away and whizzes past the outside edge.
Shorter and outside off, Wade lets it be.

EDGY FOUR! Just wide of Ben Stokes! Frustrating for England. Root floats it around off, it drifts back in but pitches and then turns away. Wade looks to drive it hard but due to the turn away, it goes off the outside edge, past the diving Stokes and down to the third man fence.
Floated delivery on middle, Smith nudges it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Smith keeps it out.

Excellent fielding by Stuart Broad. Full on middle, Smith drives it straight past the bowler through mid on. Stuart Broad from long on runs to his left and slides to save two runs for the team. The mid off fielder does the mopping up job. Also, the 100 run-stand is up between the two as they continue to bat England out of the game.
Floated delivery on middle, Smith blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Smith drives it to covers.
Flighted delivery on middle, Smith defends it out.
The straighter one now from Root on middle, defended.
Brilliant again from Root! This time there is extra bounce too. It lands on off and then spins away. Wade lunges and tries to keep it out but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Well bowled! This lands on off, it pitches and turns away. Wade tries to defend but gets beaten.
In the air but safe! Root floats it up on off, Wade looks to drive but the ball once again stops in the surface, it goes off the outer half uppishly but well short of point.
Outside off this time, Wade guides it to point.
On middle, this is kept out.
On middle, SS defends it out.
Shorter and outside off, Wade slaps it through covers for one.
Flatter and on off, Smith works it through square leg and takes one.
Another tossed up ball on off, Smith strokes it to covers.
On the pads again, Wade works it through mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Flatter and on middle, this is defended.
Misfield! The wheels seem to be coming off for England now. 300 up for Australia. This is floated up on off, Wade strokes it towards cover where the fielder lets it through and a single is taken.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads. One run added to the total.
Flighted ball on off, Smith defends it out.
A single to follow the boundary! On off, Wade taps it towards cover for one.

FOUR! He has hit that really fine! Fifty for Wade. 5th in Test cricket. He is justifying his selection in the team here. Also, it has been a very positive innings from him. Right from the start he wanted to score and he has brought it up in quick time too. He gets there by playing a reverse sweep, it goes between the legs of the keeper for a boundary in the third man region.
On middle, Wade defends it out.
Joe Root brings himself on. Trying everything here is the England skipper.

DRINKS! Australia going along really well here. Their lead is above 200 now and they have not lost a wicket after Lunch. Another decent hour for them will probably mean it is difficult for them to lose the game. England on the other hand, look flat at the moment. Their bowling does not look threatening. They need someone to put their hand up and deliver. Anyone in their side who can do so? We will have to wait to find out.
A couple to end the over! Moeen over pitches outside off. Smith drives it wide of the fielder in the deep and two is taken.

NOT OUT! Missing leg by a mile! As I wrote, it was a review in desperation. They somehow want to get Smith out, actually they somehow want a wicket. Moeen Ali tosses this on middle and it turns back in. Smith looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but the umpire shakes his head. England review and replays show that the on-field call is the right one. England lose one review.
A huge appeal for an LBW has been turned down. England review but I feel it is in desperation. Looks high and going down leg.
Another good ball! This is flatter and on middle, it once again turns away. Wade looks to defend but is squared up. It goes off the outside edge towards backward point for one.
BEATEN! This is tossed up on off, it pitches and then turns away. Wade looks to defend off the front foot but is beaten. Very few deliveries like these have been seen today.
Flatter and on middle, Wade pushes it back to the bowler.
Lead touches 200 now! On middle, Smith goes back and works it through square leg for one.
FOUR! Too short and put away! This is around off, enough time for Wade to go back and punch it through covers. Another boundary. Runs flowing freely now.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On middle, Wade defends it onto the ground.
Down the leg side, Smith looks to sweep but misses. It goes behind for a run. Bye signaled.
Almost! This lands in the rough outside leg. Smith looks to defend but the ball spits off the surface. It hits the shoulder of the bat but lobs in no man's land on the off side.
Short and on off, Wade makes room and slaps it through covers. The fielder chases it and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
Wade now takes one as he pushes it through covers and keeps strike.
Smith keeps strike as he guides it through point for one.

FOUR! Smith is now bossing the game here! England's body language seems to be dropping. The crowd here has gone quiet. It seems like they have already given up at the moment. Smith uses his feet, gets to the pitch of the ball and whips it over mid-wicket for another boundary.
FOUR! Deft! Lovely, lovely batting! Moeen Ali fires this outside off, Smith waits for it and then guides it late past slip, no one at third man so a boundary.
Floats it up on off, Smith defends it out.
Flatter and on off, Wade pushes it through covers with the turn for one. Too easy at the moment for the two.
Floats it up on middle, Smith looks to flick but does so early. A soft leading edge back to the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, this is defended.
Very full and outside off, Wade drives it square on the off side for one.
FOUR! Reverse sweep and a boundary! Wade sees it is outside off and there is a lot of flight on it. He goes down on one knee and hits it through short third man for a boundary.
Flatter and around off, Wade goes back and keeps it out.
This is bowled outside off, it turns back in. Wade gets his front pad out of the way and tries to defend but misses to get hit on the front pad. A huge appeal but it is an ambitious one.
Another sweep shot towards deep backward square leg for another run.
Way too short, Smith pulls it hard but there is a man at deep mid-wicket so only a single.
Floats it up on off, Smith lunges and defends it out.
Flatter and outside off, Smith goes back and keeps it out.
Wade now plays the sweep shot, hits it nicely through backward square leg for one.
Smith initially looks to play the paddle sweep but then seeing the length, adjusts and works it through square leg for one.
Moeen Ali is on now.
Now Wade bends and blocks it to see through the over.
Outside off, Wade lunges and pads it away.
On the pads again, Steve whips it to mid-wicket for one.
Very full on the pads, SS defends it back towards the bowler.
Flighted around off, Wade strokes it towards cover for a single.
Floated on leg, Smith reverse sweeps it behind square on the off side for a single.
Length delivery outside off, MW has no business with it.
FOUR! And the crowd has gone silent! Brings up the 50-run stand too. Woakes bowls this down the leg side, Wade helps it on it's way to the fine leg fence for a boundary. Lead moves to 168 now.
Outside off, Wade stands tall and punches it to the right of backward point but the fielder dives on that side and saves runs for his side. The crowd suddenly getting loud again.
Length delivery outside off, Wade helps it down towards backward point.
Good length ball on off, Wade defends it off the front foot.
Full on middle and off, Smith turns it behind square on the leg side and gets a single as the fielder from fine leg cleans it up.
A dot to end as Wade works this with the turn towards square leg.
Uppish but safe! This is tossed up outside off, Wade looks to drive it but the ball sticks in the surface. He ends up hitting it uppishly but well short of the bowler.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
Floats it up on off, Wade lunges and keeps it out.
Off the glove! This is floated up outside off, Wade looks to reverse sweep but it hits the glove and lobs over the keeper and down towards fine leg for two.
Smith misses out there! A drag down by Denly on middle, Smith goes back and looks to pull it hard but mistimes it through mid-wicket for one.
Joe Denly is back into the attack.

Inside edge saves Wade there. Something happened out of nothing there. This is on a good length around off and it stays very low. Wade just about gets his bat down in time and he gets an inside edge onto the pads. A huge shout by the bowler but the umpire shakes his head.
This is angled into the pads, Smith works it down to fine leg for one. 250 up for Australia. The lead is 160.
Slower one around off, Smith plays it with soft hands to the man at point.
Goes wide of the crease and angles into the off pole, Smith defends it onto the ground.
A lovely shot but just for one! Fuller and around off, Wade leans into it and strokes it through covers for one.
One more cutter on off, Wade plays it late towards point.
Another one outside off, maybe after that boundary, Broad does not want to bowl on the stumps anymore. Smith shoulders arms to it.
Another one outside off and it is on a length. Smith lets it be.
Goes back to bowling outside off and the length is fuller. Smith looks to drive but gets an outside edge towards backward point.

FOUR! Need not run for those! That was just dismissive. Broad goes full and on middle, looking to surprise Smith by bowling one on the stumps. Smith is up for the task, he shows the full face of the bat and creams it to the long on fence.
Good delivery and well played! Broad bowls this fuller around off, it tails back in a little. Wade moves his front leg out of the way and works it wide of mid on for one.
Broad from around the wicket lands it on off, it is blocked.
Shorter in length and around off, Wade swivels and pulls it through mid-wicket. There is a man in the deep so just a run. He keeps strike.
Good change in pace! It is a slower one on middle, Wade looks to flick but does so early. A soft leading edge is induced back to the bowler.
Closer to the off pole this time, Wade gets his bat down and keeps it out.
Another one on a length and outside off, Wade shoulders arms to this one.

Length this time but the line is once again outside off, Wade lets it be. Woakes is trying to do what he did in the first innings. Continuously taking it out and then trying to get one back in. There is just no swing available though.
Fuller and outside off, Wade makes a leave.
Continues bowling harmless deliveries, outside off. Smith lets it be.
A crowd catch there! Broad goes full and around off, Smith strokes it into the ground and then it goes to the short cover fielder.
One more ball outside off, Smith need not play at those.
On a good length and outside off, Smith lets it be. Bairstow has a shy at the stumps at his end but hits Smith. The keeper straightaway apologizes.
On the fuller side and around off, Smith strokes it to covers.
Fuller and outside off, Smith leaves it alone.
This time he bowls it on middle and it angles away. Wade goes back and keeps it out.
Angles this away from the off pole, Wade does not bother playing at it.
FOUR! Wade is dealing in boundaries! Lead above 150 now. Fuller and outside off, Wade strokes it square on the off side, it is in the gap and the ball races away to the fence.
Fuller and around off, Smith strokes it to mid off.
Another one outside off, Wade does not fiddle with it.
Slightly fuller and outside off, Wade shoulders arms to this one.
A single to end the over! On the pads, it is worked down to fine leg for one.
Fuller and around off, Smith drives it through cover-point. There is a sweeper in the deep so only one.
Another leave as Broad bowls it outside off again.
Continues bowling it outside off, it is left alone again.

FOUR! 100 for Steve Smith. Back-to-back tons and 5th Australian to score two centuries in a single Ashes Test. What a player, what a player he is! What a comeback from him! Absolutely brilliant. This would be a big, big moment and an emotional one too for him. The English fans are heard booing him as he takes his helmet off and celebrates but he won't care and instead enjoy the moment. He gets to his ton in style. Broad bowls it full and around off, Smith creams it between two short cover fielders and past normal covers for a boundary. He needs no reminding though that his job is still not done. It is his 25th Test ton.
Way too wide outside off, bowling to his field is Broad as he has 7 fielders on the off side. Smith lets it be.
Stuart Broad to bowl from the other end.
On a good length on middle, Wade tucks it to mid-wicket. Just a run from the over.
Outside off, Wade lets it go.
On a good length and outside off, Wade shoulders his arms to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Wade blocks it off the back foot.
On a length on leg, Wade flicks it to mid-wicket.
Smith moves onto 99 as he scores off the first ball of this session. On the pads, Smith works it down to fine leg for one.

We are back for the second session on Day 4. The English players are in a huddle before they take their positions in the field. Steve Smith, who is on 98 walks out along with Matthew Wade to resume their innings. Chris Woakes will finally get the ball today. He did not bowl a single over in the first session.
... Day 4, Session 2 ...

England have not looked at their best with the ball today. Broad did bowl a few good deliveries but not consistently. Moeen Ali too did not look a lot threatening. Denly did get a lot of purchase off the surface but he was guilty of bowling at least one bad ball in each over. Stokes is the only wicket-taker but never looked at his best. The interesting thing though is, Woakes was not used at all, not sure what the reason was. One would expect him to bowl after the break. England would hope for some quick wickets after the Lunch interval. Will they be able to do so or will Australia continue to dominate? Join us in a while to find out.

The day started with Head and Smith continuing from where they left off yesterday. They added a massive 130-run stand and took Australia's lead past the 100-run mark. Head got to his fifty and was looking set for a big score but Stokes got him slashing to a ball outside off which saw his downfall. Wade however, has come out with positive intent and the two are amidst a 26-run stand. Australia will know, one good partnership and they will probably bat England out of the game. Smith though holds the key, he is on 98 and the visitors would hope the rest bat around him.

Is there any doubt which side will be the happier heading into the break? If yes, the quiet crowd here will probably indicate that. Yes, it is Australia who are slightly ahead in the game at the moment and once again, it is Steve Smith who is the hero for them.
Smith will have to wait for his second hundred of this Test. Floated on off, Smith milks it to long on and gets a single. LUNCH ON DAY 4.
Shorter on off, Smith defends it off his back foot.
Flighted outside off, Steve drives it hard but to the man at cover.
Floated on off, Smith taps it back to the bowler.
Sharp spin. Shorter outside off, Smith looks to defend but the ball hits him on his thigh pad.
Shorter on off, Smith flicks it to square leg.
Moeen Ali is back into the attack. He was wayward in his first spell today, let's see how he bowls now.
Full on off, Wade defends it towards short cover and calls wait to his partner.
Misses his line again and bowls one down the leg side. Wade looks to flick but misses.
Short ball outside off, Wade sways away from it. Typical pace bowler's response after being hit for a boundary.
FOUR! Wade moves to 15 in a flash. Full on the pads, Wade flicks it through mid-wicket to get his third boundary of the innings already.
Full down the leg side, Wade looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
On the pads, Wade glances it to the on side and keeps the strike.
Floated outside off, MW leaves it alone.
Shorter on off, Wade keeps it away off his back foot.
Spins away a lot. Pitches it on the rough outside off, Wade leaves it alone and the ball goes wide of leg pole.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Flighted outside off, Wade gets on his front foot and thrashes it through covers for a boundary.
Flighted outside off, Wade leaves it alone.
Full once again on off, Smith pushes it to mid off.
Fuller on off, Smith shuffles across and flicks it towards square leg for a couple. Moves 3 runs closer to a well-deserved ton.
NO BALL! Stokes oversteps once again. He bowls it full outside off, Smith shoulders arms to it.
Short ball around leg pole. Smith ducks under it.
Fuller on off, Steve gets behind it and blocks it.
Length ball around off, Smith hits it straight to point.
Full ball outside off, Smith pushes it to cover.
In the air but wide of the fielder. Flighted outside off, Matthew gets down and sweeps it wide of leg gully and gets a couple as Moeen Ali from deep mid-wicket cleans it up.
Tossed up outside off, Matthew pads it away.
That excited the England players. Floated outside off, Wade looks to sweep but misses and the ball hits the shoulder of Matthew.
Floats it on the stumps, Wade defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Denly is guilty of overpitching it outside off, Wade picks it early and drives it through covers to get off the mark.
Very full on middle and leg, Smith strokes it wide of mid on for one and moves to 95.
Another short ball, Smith pulls this towards deep mid-wicket for one.
Very good field placement! Stokes bends his back and bowls it short. Smith pulls it in a controlled manner which goes to leg gully on the bounce.
Bouncer! Steve ducks under it.
Length ball on off, Smith looks to flick but gets a leading edge towards point which goes all along the ground.
FOUR! Smith is unfazed by the wicket. Stokes bowls a length ball on off, Smith drives it on the up and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Smith pushes it towards point.
Smith retains strike as he whips this fuller ball on leg through mid-wicket for one.
Very full on middle, Smith pushes it back to the bowler.
Shorter in length and pitches in the rough. Smith initially looks to flick but seeing the turn away, he keeps it out.
Gives it a lot of air and lands it on middle, Smith keeps it out.
Another loopy ball around middle, this is a little too full. Smith pushes it to mid off.
Floats it up around leg, Smith lunges and keeps it out.
Matthew Wade walks out to bat now.

OUT! Caught behind! Head departs after getting to his fifty! The slower ball has done the trick for England! A wicket against the run of play but England will take it with both hands. Their Test vice-captain has given his side the much-needed breakthrough. Stokes steams in and bowls a good length delivery outside off, Head goes for the cut. Stokes however, had rolled his fingers on the delivery and hence the ball arrives slower than what Travis anticipated and also it bounces a little more. It takes the outside edge and goes towards the keeper. Bairstow dives in front and takes a very good low catch. Crucial wicket this as the duo of Smith and Head was taking the game away from the hosts. The umpires also check for the no ball but that too is fine. The 130-run stand is broken. Australia lead by 115 runs. England will now hope this opens the floodgates.
Stokes misses the line again as throws this wide on the leg side but Head misses his flick.
This was coming in from the short of length, Head hangs back and blocks it easily.
This is outside off, there's room for Head who slaps it towards point for nothing.
On the shorter length, aiming the top of off stump, Head pushes it towards mid on.
On the middle and leg, Smith tucks it towards leg side and takes off for a quick single. There's a shy at the striker's end but no direct hit. The batsman was in anyways.
Single to end the over. On the pads, Steve glances it to the on side and gets a single.
Floated on leg, SS defends it off the front foot.
Shorter on off, Steve defends it off the back foot.
Flighted on the stumps, Steve defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Two in two and Smith is going after the part-timer. Brings the 200 up in style. Floated on leg, Steve whips it away though mid-wicket again to get another boundary.
FOUR! Whipped and whipped away! Floated on the pads, Smith smashes it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! Head gets to his fifty in style! Length ball outside off, Travis punches it through backward point and gets a boundary to bring up his 6th Test fifty. He has played a brilliant innings here. He generally gets out after getting off to a start but this time he has got to the fifty-run mark and now would be eyeing a big score.
Short ball outside off, Head sways it away.
Brilliant fielding! Length ball outside off, Head punches it towards point. Burns at point dives to his right and saves a certain boundary.
Smith shuffles across and turns it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Good length ball on off, SS defends it off the front foot.
Slower ball on off, Smith defends it off the front foot.
On the pads, SS turns it behind square on the leg side for one.  The lead now  is of 100.
Tossed up around off, TH gets down and sweeps it to square leg for one.
Floated on the stumps, Head defends it off the front foot.

Bairstow has missed a stumping chance! Flighted outside off, Head comes ahead and looks to defend but loses his balance. He misses the ball but luckily for him, the ball hits Bairstow's pads who is late to get down. It is not a straightforward chance but England need to take these chances at the moment. They need a breakthrough and need to be extra alert.
Floated around leg, Smith whips it to the on side for one.
Loopy ball on the pads, Smith blocks it.
Good length ball outside off, TH shoulders arms to it.
Chance! This was in the air. Very close to the short mid-wicket fielder. This was angling in as Smith flicked it wide off the short mid-wicket fielder to get a single.
Down the leg side, Smith leaves it alone.
FOUR! Another fuller ball outside off stump, Smith times it sweetly towards cover-point to get another boundary.
FOUR! Stokes goes for a shorter ball but the line is outside off, Smith guides it through the third man region to get a boundary.
Bowls a little fuller on the off stump, Smith lunges and blocks it well.
NO BALL! Stokes oversteps! He bowls it on a length on off, Smith blocks it.
Loopy ball on the stumps, TH blocks it.
Flighted on off, Travis blocks it.
OHH! Very full on middle and leg, Head initially looks to sweep but then defends it.
Very well bowled. Floats it outside off on the rough. The ball keeps low and beats Head's defensive blade.
Bowls it on the rough, it spins in. Smith looks to defend but the ball kisses his pads and goes behind for a single.
Floats it on leg, Smith defends it. Smart bowling as there is a lot of rough outside Smith's leg stump.

Drinks Break! Australia's hour. The duo of Head and Smith has continued from where they left off on Day 3. England have struggled to trouble the pair. Though there is spin and bounce, Moeen has struggled with his line and length. The hosts need to break this stand as they are taking the game away from them slowly like a poison.
Good length ball outside off, Head strokes it towards mid off of the inner half of his bat.
On top of off, Travis defends it back to the bowler.
On the pads, TH glances it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Head nudges it fine down the leg side and gets a couple to bring up the century stand between the duo.
Another one down the leg side but inside the tramline.
Corrects his line and bowls it on off, Head punches it to point.
WIDE! Stokes misses the line way too much and sends this one down the leg side and away from the tramline. Wided by the umpire.
WOW! That has turned leaps and bounds. Pitches it on the rough outside off, it spins so much that it goes outside leg. Bairstow fails to take it cleanly allowing them to steal a bye.
Floated on off, Smith whips it towards mid-wicket and gets a single.
Tossed up on off, Smith comes down and blocks it.
Floated on off, Smith keeps it out.
Shorter and pitching on the rough. Head waits and then punches it through covers for a run.
Starts with a flighted ball outside off, Smith strokes it to cover for one.
Change from both the ends. Joe Denly replaces Moeen Ali. Has not been a good morning for Moeen so far.
A solid front foot defense to get through the over.
On middle, Head defends it with authority.
Very full on the pads, Head defends it to mid on.
Ohh! Full on off, Head looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length ball outside off, Stokes punches it to point.
Starts with a full ball on off. Head plays a solid push to mid off.
First bowling change of the day. Ben Stokes is into the attack now.
Slower through the air on off, Steve defends it off the front foot.
Shorter on off, TH punches it to cover for a single.
FOUR! Moeen struggles to bowl his best balls continuously. He bowls a rank full toss on off, Head strokes it through mid on for a boundary.
Off spinner on off, Smith glances it towards mid-wicket for one.
Shorter on off, Smith waits and defends it off the back foot.
Flights it on off, Smith defends it off the front foot.
Fuller on off, TH pushes it off the front foot.
Length delivery outside off, Head looks to punch and goes to point.
Full on off, Head drives it through covers. Archer dives to his right but misfields allowing them to take two.
For the umpteenth time the 8-ball gauge is out. Nothing doing.
Full on off, TH blocks it off the front foot.
Full on off, TH defends it off the front foot.
Misses his line and bowls it down the leg side. Head looks to flick but misses.
Shorter on off, Head punches it towards cover for a single.
Ripper! Flights it on off, Head looks to defend but the ball grips away and beats the outside edge. Bairstow takes the bails off quickly but no casualty.
Flighted outside off, Smith pushes it towards cover and gets to the other end.
Ohh! Floated on off, Smith looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge. The ball goes fine down the leg side and gets a couple.
Shorter outside off, Smith stands tall and punches it through covers for a couple.
Floated on off, Smith whips it to mid-wicket.
Good bowling. Full on middle and leg, Head defends it off the front foot.
The 8-ball gauge is out once again. And just like it has happened throughout this Test, the umpire gives it back to the bowler.
This one comes in with the angle, Head defends it towards point.
Once again follows  the boundary with a solid defense towards cover.

FOUR! Second boundary of the over. Once again Broad bowls it full on the pads, Head flicks it with ease through mid-wicket for a boundary. Travis is looking very good out in the middle. Moves to 35 now.
Better. Back of a length ball on off, Head hops and defends it towards cover-point.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Head! Broad bowls it on the pads, Head just helps it fine down the leg side for a boundary. Brings up the 150 for Australia.
Floated on off, Head nudges it towards cover-point and calls for a quick run. Travis looses his bat but gets to the other end.
Play and miss! Shorter outside off, Head goes back and looks to cut but misses.
This one keeps low too. Flighted outside off, Head leaves it alone.
Shorter on off, Head cuts it to point.
Better. This one is pitched behind and keeps low. Head does well to defend it.
Very full on off, Head pushes it back to the bowler. Moeen will not get turn if he bowls so full.
Broad goes fuller this time, Smith lunges and keeps it out.
Another one on the off pole, Smith defends it onto the ground off the back foot. He is playing with soft hands which is ideal on this surface.
That is a beauty! Broad comes running in and angles it into the off pole, the batter has to play at it. He tries to defend but the ball straightens and beats the outside edge.
Good length and outside off, Smith moves outside off and makes a leave. The ball hits the pads and goes to the keeper.
On the pads, Head works it towards fine leg for an easy run.
Fuller in length and coming back in from off. Smith looks to drive it through the off side but it goes off the inner half past the bowler for one.
Very full on middle and leg, TH pushes it to mid on. 4 easy singles off the over.
On the pads, Smith turns it to the on side and rotates the strike.
Shorter on off, Head punches it towards cover-point and rotates the strike.
Flighted on the pads, Smith glances it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Flighted on off, Head pushes it wide of cover and gets a single.
Floated on middle and leg, Head keeps it out.
Good length delivery on leg, Smith looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.

FOUR! Uppish but in the gap. First mistimed shot from Smith. Full on off, Smith lofts his drive uppishly through mid off and cover. He does not time it well but the placement is so good as the fielders there just watch it dissect them. Australia lead by 50 runs. The visitors are effectively 50/3.
Good length ball on off, Smith lunges forward and blocks it away.
Broad delivers this inswinging ball on off, Steve taps it back towards the bowler.
Closer to off stump, Steve defends it off the front foot.
Length ball on off, it raises just a notch. Smith looks to defend but does so off the upper half of his bat.
Floated on middle, Head pushes it to mid on.
Tossed up outside off, TH leaves it alone.

FOUR BYES! Absolute beauty from Moeen. It beats everyone. Ali prefers bowling to Head rather than Smith. He flights it on middle and off, Head looks to defend but the ball spins away beating the outside edge of Head's willow. It goes between the legs of Bairstow too and to the fence.
Off spinner on middle, Steve glances it away with the spin towards fine leg for one.
Tossed up on off, Smith defends it off the front foot.
Slower through the air on off, Smith flicks it to the right of short leg but keeps it down.
Another top nut to finish the over. The previous one went away and this one has come in. Pitches outside off, Head shoulders arms to it but the ball just about misses the stumps.
Beauty! This is pitched just outside off, Head this time goes to defend it but the ball swings away and just about misses the outside edge of Travis' bat.
Length delivery outside off, tempting Head to drive but he does not go chasing after it and leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Head pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, it comes in but Head is aware of his off pole and leaves it alone.

Fifty for Smith. His 25th in Test cricket. Warner and Bancroft have had a bad return but Steve has showed his class in the very first Test of his return. He gets to the milestone with a guide towards third man. It is appreciated and also booed by the fans but Smith continues to be a thorn in England's way. He raises his bat but then he gets back at his work.
On the stumps again. TH lunges and defends it onto the ground.
Another flighted ball on middle, Head defends it out.
Close! This is floated around off, it turns back in. Smith looks to defend but it goes off the inner half, past short leg for one.
Good fielding again! This time by the short leg fielder. Shorter and on middle, Smith goes back and works it to the right of that fielder. He dives and also saves a single.
Good fielding by Roy! Smith whips this with the turn towards mid-wicket. Roy there dives to his right and makes a half-stop. Gets to his feet quickly and stops a run.
Flatter and on off, Smith goes back and keeps it out.
One more leave to end the over! Outside off, Head does not fiddle with it. A maiden to begin with by Broad.
One more delivery outside off, it has been left alone.
On the off stump this time and it is on a length. Head is solid in defense.
Way too wide outside off this time, Head lets it be.

Another appeal! Head this time is late in his shot but once again it is going down with the angle. This is fuller and on the pads, Head looks to flick but is late in the shot. It hits him on the pads. The appeal is waved away again. Hawk Eye confirms that it has pitched outside leg.

A huge shout straightaway! However, this is sliding down leg. Broad steams in from around the wicket and bowls it fuller around leg. Head looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Broad makes a huge appeal but the umpire shakes his head. There is a discussion between the bowler, Root and Bairstow but they decide not to review.
Stuart Broad to bowl from the other end.
Edged but safe. Shorter on off, Head looks to cut but gets a thick outside edge which flies towards third man. Head takes a single and keeps the strike. 5 runs off the first over of the day.
Floated on the pads, Steve glances it to the leg side and gets to the other end.

NO BALL! Smart thinking but gets nothing off it. Moeen sees Smith coming down the track so he bowls an overhead full toss. Smith looks to play the tennis shot but misses. Bairstow looks to stump but he fails to gather. Would not have mattered even if Bairstow had collected that as he could not have stumped him off a no ball. The idea from Moeen was to lob it over Smith's head and hit the stumps. Ambitious but worth a shot.
Also, some news about Anderson, he won't be bowling in this innings for England. He would bat IF needed.
Shorter on off, Head punches it to cover and gets his first run of the day.
Straighter on off, Head defends it off the front foot.
Comes around the wicket and flights one on middle and leg. Head defends it off the front foot.
This one has not raised at all. Flighted on the pads, the ball keeps down as low as Smith's ankle. Steve turns it behind square on the leg side and gets a single.

We are all set to start Day 4 of the 1st Test. The English players walk out to the middle to a huge applause from the crowd. Overnight batsmen, Steve Smith and Travis Head then follow them out to the middle but they are welcomed with a huge echos of boos by the English supporters. Moeen Ali to bowl the first over of the game.

Lead - 34, wickets in hand - 7, Smith and Head's partnership - 49. That is where Australia begin Day 4. The pendulum in this match is right in the balance as we begin another exciting day of Test cricket. The opening hour will be very crucial for both sides as a couple of wickets will see the balance of power shift to the hosts but if the overnight pair see out this phase then one will have to put Australia on top as there is turn and bounce on offer for the spinners. Historically, Day 4 has been a very crucial day at Edgbaston and that won't change in this game as this back and forth game might just put someone in the driver's seat today. So on this action packed Sunday we welcome you to the coverage of the penultimate day of the first Ashes Test.
... Day 4, Morning Session ....

Will England continue their dominance in this Test or will Australia's fight in the final session of Day 3 work as a spark in fire? Join us on Sunday, 4th August, 2019 for Day 4 at 1100 Local (1000 GMT). Till then, Goodbye!

End of a topsy-turvy Day 3 here in Birmingham. Australia would have liked to bowl England out under the lead of 50 but failed to do so. England, on the other hand, would have loved to pick up a couple of more wickets by the end of the day. Both failed in their mission but it was the visitors who ended the day on a strong note scoring 124 runs in the last session.

After early Tea, the hosts came out with venom as they sent both, Warner and Bancroft early. Usman Khawaja and Steve Smith though counter attacked and steadied the ship adding 48 runs together. The former looked good but fell against the run of play. Travis Head then joined the Australian hero of the 1st innings and just like in the first innings, they fought hard and ensured there were no more casualties as Australia ended the day early due to bad light.

That would be the last of Day 3 as the umpires call stumps due to bad light. Australia started the day on the front foot picking up 4 wickets for 33 runs. It looked like they would not get to a lead of even 50 but Woakes and Broad had other ideas as the duo added 65 runs for the 9th wicket which helped England take a 90-run lead.

Stuart Broad is into the attack but he might not get to bowl as umpire Aleem Dar is having a word with Root. Looks like it is too dark and seamers cannot bowl now. Root takes the ball away from Broad. The Light meter is now brought on and oh no! We are going off the field. The umpires are not happy and the players are off the field due to bad light.
This keeps low but luckily, there is no casualty. Good length ball outside off, the ball keeps low and comes in. Luckily it does not nip in enough to hit Head's pad or the stumps.
Outside off, Head has no business with this one and leaves it alone.
On top of off, Head defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length ball on off, SS pulls it all along the ground towards mid-wicket for a single.
Now drives but straight to the man at point.
FOUR! Pulled and pulled away hard! Short ball on off, Smith picks it early and pulls it in a controlled manner through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on off, Head defends it out.
Short again, Head cuts it to point.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries for Travis Head. Short and outside off, Head cuts it hard through point for a boundary.
FOUR! In the air but safe. Shorter ball outside off, Head looks to cut but ends up slicing it wide. Luckily the ball goes wide and away of the man at first slip to the third man fence.
Flighted delivery outside off, Head lets it go.
Tossed up wide outside off, Head leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Smith defends it off the front foot.
On the pads, Smith flicks it but straight to square leg.
This time Smith pulls the short ball in a controlled manner towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.
The physio is out now having a look at Smith. Luckily though he looks be fine to continue his innings here.

NASTY! Stokes bends his back and bowls a vicious short ball. Smith looks to pull but the ball goes through and hits him flush on the grill. The England players gather around Smith. He removes his helmet but will have a mandatory check here as per the protocol. Steve nods though indicating everything is all right.
On a good length on off, Smith plays it to point.
On the pads, Smith turns it to the on side and gets a single.
Tossed up on off, Head pushes it towards cover for a single.
On the pads, Head flicks it to mid-wicket.
Floated on the stumps, Head defends it off the front foot.
Shorter on off, Head punches it to cover.
Pitches it on the rough outside off, Head leaves it alone.
Defended off the back foot by Smith.
NO BALL! Good length ball outside off, Smith leaves it alone.

Huge appeal for lbw but nothing from the umpire. Good length ball around off, Smith looks to defend but misses. The ball hits him below his box. The  English players put in a huge appeal but nothing from the umpire. Stokes thinks it is dipping but Root does not feel it is dipping enough to overturn the decision.
Fuller on off, Smith pushes it to mid off.
On top of off, Smith flicks it to square leg and shouts wait on to his partner.
