Good length ball outside off, Smith leaves it alone in his trademark fashion.
Stokes misses his line and bowls it down the leg side. Steve leaves it alone.
Very full on middle and leg, Head pushes it to mid on.
Flighted on off, Steve whips it to mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
This keeps low! Floated on middle, Smith does well to negate the low bounce and turn it to mid-wicket.
Good running. Floated on off, Head defends it with soft hands towards cover and calls for a quick single. He gets to the other end with ease.
Shorter on middle, Smith punches it wide of mid on and gets a single.
FOUR! Gorgeous! Moeen tosses it up on off, Smith gets on his front foot and creams it through covers for a boundary.
On the hips, Head tucks it fine down the leg side and gets a couple. It also brings up the 100 for Australia.
Back of a length ball on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.
On the pads, Head glances it but cannot get past mid-wicket.
Length ball on the pads, Head glances it to mid-wicket.
Length ball outside off, Head goes for the punch but ends up chopping it back towards the keeper.

Direct hit and Head was gone for all money! Good length ball on off, Smith shuffles across and tucks it towards mid-wicket. Burns comes running in from square leg and gets to the ball quickly. He has one stump to aim at the keeper's end but misses.

Drinks Break! Australia have got the lead but have already lost 3 wickets. The duo of Head and Smith hold the key here for Australia. Tim Paine would hope that these two continue their good work and increase their lead. England will look to break this stand and further their grip on this game.
On the pads, Smith flicks it away to the on side and keeps the strike.
Floated on off, Smith defends it by bending his back.

Huge appeal but the impact looked to be outside off. Flighted delivery outside off, it spins in and keeps low. Smith looks to defend but misses. The ball hits his back pad and Bairstow goes up in appeal but nothing from the umpire.
On the pads, Smith waits and turns it towards fine leg and gets a couple.
Floated on off, Head defends it with soft hands towards cover and gets a single.
Flighted on off, Head strokes it wide of mid off.
A huge cheer from the crowd as Archer comes on as a substitute fielder.
On off pole, Smith defends it back to the bowler.
Length delivery outside off, Smith shuffles across and leaves it alone. The ball kisses his pad and goes to the keeper.
On off, Smith turns it wide of fine leg and gets a couple as Moeen Ali cleans it up.
Root, Broad, Buttler and Stokes gather around and are having a chat.
Full on off, Head tucks it against the angle towards mid-wicket and gets a single.
On the fourth stump line, Head leaves it alone.
Into the lead now! Good length ball on off, Smith glances it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Australia level the scores now. Smith flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets a single which nullifies Australia's deficit.
Tossed up outside off, Smith reaches out and drives it to mid off.
Flights it on off, Smith calmly defends it.
Floated on off, Head strokes it wide of cover for one.
Tossed up on off, Smith drives it through covers. The ball does not have the legs to reach the fence as the fielder cleans it up. The batsmen come back for the third.
Flighted on off, Smith defends it off the front foot.
Fuller outside off, TH shoulders arms to it.
On the pads, Head glances it towards mid-wicket and gets a brace as the fielder cleans it up.
On the fourth stump line, Head leaves it alone.
Length ball on off, Head looks to defend but it comes off the bottom half of his bat.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Smith turns it behind square on the leg side and gets a single.
Length delivery on the pads, Smith glances it towards mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Tossed up on off, Head defends it off the front foot to see off Moeen Ali's over.

FOUR RUNNING RUNS! Schoolboy stuff from England. Floated delivery on  middle and leg, Head flicks it through mid-wicket and they come back for the third. Roy has a shy at the keeper's end. The ball bounces just in front of Bairstow and deflects behind of his pads towards the third man region allowing them to take one more.
Outside off, left alone.
Floated outside off, Head shoulders arms to this one.
Bowls it very full to Travis first up. Head defends it with a straight bat.
Floated on off, Smith turns it behind square on the leg side and gets a single.
Just a solitary over for Root as Moeen Ali comes back.
Outside off and Head leaves it alone. Brilliant start for Stokes. Wicket maiden for him to begin.
Bouncer! It is a well directed one but Travis sits under it.
Length delivery outside off, Travis leaves it alone.
Another gem! Good length ball on middle and off, it comes in and cuts Head in half on its way to the keeper.
Travis Head is the new man in.

OUT! Caught! This is a peach of a delivery from Stokes! He bowls a scrambled seam delivery on off, it nips back in cutting Khawaja in half. He looks to defend but the ball kisses his inside edge and carries to the right of the keeper. Bairstow moves to that side and takes a good catch. The English players go up in a very confident appeal and the umpire agrees. Once again the bowling change has worked for the hosts. Khawaja cannot convert his good start here and the 48-run stand is broken. Australia still trail by 15 runs.
Starts with a good length ball around off. It does not come very quickly. Khawaja defends it to mid off.
Change from both the ends. Ben Stokes comes in place of Chris Woakes.
Slower on off, Khawaja strokes it towards extra cover and keeps the strike with a single.
Flights one on off, Khawaja plays a textbook front foot defense to it.
Tossed up on off, Khawaja defends it off the front foot.
Once again away from the off pole, Usman has nothing to do with it.
Floated outside off, Khawaja leaves it alone.
Starts with a flighted delivery on the pads, Smith glances it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Skipper, Joe Root has got himself into the attack now.
FOUR! This is even better than the previous boundary. Woakes overpitches it on middle and leg, Khawaja plays a handsome on drive through mid on for a boundary.
Outside off, Khawaja leaves it alone without any fuss.
Follows it up with a good, solid front foot defense.
FOUR! Beautiful! Full outside off, Khawaja gets on his front foot and drives it excellently through covers. The fielders from point and cover give it a chase but cannot stop it.
On the pads, Smith nudges it to fine leg for a single.

Could have been disastrous! Back of a length ball around off, Smith shuffles in and defends it towards cover-point. He comes ahead for a single but Khawaja sends him back. Good and early call as there was never a run there. Run out is the last thing the Aussies need at the moment.
Floated on off, UK pushes it to cover to get through the over.
Off spinner pitching on off. It spins in and  Smith turns it behind square on the leg side with the spin for a single.
Tossed up on off, Smith looks to flick it towards mid-wicket but gets a leading edge which goes all along the ground back to the bowler.
Shorter around off, Smith gets on his back foot and defends it.
Comes around the wicket and flights it on off. Khawaja milks it down to long off for one.
Tossed up on off, Smith glances it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Fuller on middle, Khawaja flicks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple as the fielder mops it up. Usman is looking good out in the middle but he needs to continue this.
Ouch! Back of a length ball on off, Khawaja looks to defend but the ball hits him very high on his bat. Jarring the bottom hand.
Fuller on off, Khawaja defends it back towards Woakes.
Length ball pitching on off, it goes away with the angle. Khawaja leaves  it alone.
Good length ball on off, Smith shuffles like his usual self and flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller on off, Smith defends it with a straight bat.
Very full, almost a yorker on off. Khawaja does well to get his bat down in time.
Shorter on off, Khawaja defends it by getting right behind that on his back foot.
Flighted on off, Smith milks it down to long on for one.
Tossed up around off, Usman strokes it to the left of cover and gets to the other end.
Flighted on off, Khawaja drives it straight to cover.
Flighted around off, Smith comes down the track and whips it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller on off, Smith pushes it towards cover for a single.
EDGED BUT SHORT! Good length ball outside off, it comes in. Smith looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. Luckily he played it with soft hands which meant it fell well short of Bairstow.
Length ball outside off, Smith looks to defend but once again misses and gets hit high on the thigh pad.
On top of middle and off, Smith shuffles across and glances it towards square leg for a couple.
Length delivery on off, Steve defends it off the middle this time to cover.
Bowls a fuller ball outside off, it comes in after pitching. Smith looks to defend but the ball hits his thigh pad. There is a stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Woakes to bowl after the break.

Drinks Break! England needed early wickets and they have got two. Australia have lost both their openers and still trail the hosts by 38 runs. The ball is spinning and gripping so if that is an indication of the things to come, the Aussie batsman will have to play with a lot of calm and composure if they are to get a good lead in the game but first they would like to end the deficit without any further damage.
Short on off, Khawaja punches it to cover.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Moeen sprays this on the pads, Khawaja flicks it fine down the leg side and fetches himself another boundary.

BEATEN! Sharp turn on this one., It pitches around off and spins away. Khawaja looks to defend but gets beaten by the turn. That was not far away from the outside edge. Bairstow fails to collect it behind the stumps.
Tossed up on the stumps, Usman defends it off the front foot.
Flighted on off, Khawaja blocks it off the front foot.
Shorter on off, Khawaja tucks it to mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Outside off, Smith strokes it towards point and gets a brace to end the over. Expensive over from Broad. 13 runs off it.
Good length ball outside off, Smith runs it down to third man, wide of the fielder and gets a couple.
On the pads, Khawaja tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Outside off, Khawaja has nothing to do with it.
FOUR! Poor from Broad. He bowls it on the hips of Khawaja, he just nudges it fine down the leg side to get the second boundary in the over.

So that is it from the first Test of this year's Ashes. It is Australia who take a 1-0 lead and they also win the first game of the World Test Championship. The whole Test match was a roller coaster ride. If this is anything to go by, it is going to be a cracking series. The second Test is to be played at Lord's on the 14th of August 2019. It begins at 1100 local (1000 GMT). Till then, take care and goodbye!
MAN OF THE MATCH - Steve Smith for his magnificent tons in both the innings. There was absolutely no doubt about him being given the award. It is because of him, Australia won this game.

Day 5 though saw the Aussie bowlers blow away the England batting line-up. Cummins and Nathan Lyon being the stars with both sharing 10 wickets amongst them. An outstanding display of character was shown by the Aussies in this game. They were booed and bullied throughout the game by the English fans, but they never let it get into their heads and, they came out on top that too convincingly.

Despite that fightback, England batted extremely well and ended Day 2 on 267 for 4 with Rory Burns scoring a ton. They would have surely eyed a lead in excess of 150 but the Australian bowlers bowled brilliantly on the morning of Day 3 and ensured England did not take their lead past 100 which saw the game evenly poised. However, three wickets even before the deficit was wiped off, surely made England favorites. Yet again though Steve Smith and another comeback man, Matthew Wade, batted England out of the game with tons. Australia managed to score 487, giving England a target of 398 which was impossible to chase on the last day but a draw was on the cards.

Now then, the scorecard suggests, Australia won by 251 runs but the game was never so one-sided as it suggests. Instead, for the first three days, it seemed like, it would be England who would take a 1-0 lead. They had Australia on the mat after the visitors elected to bat at 122 for 8 courtesy a fifer from Broad. However, the comeback men, rose to the occasion. Smith showed why he is one of the best going around with a brilliant ton. Siddle hung around with him and his knock also proved to be very handy. Also, a crucial last wicket stand saw Australia get to a competitive first innings score.

What a performance from the Australian bowlers today! They have breached the Edgbaston fortress. Well, one would assume there might not be a lot of difference in a 4th day wicket and a 5th day wicket but it seemed like Australia bowled on a completely different surface than what England bowled on yesterday. They managed to take 4 wickets in the first session and 6 in around an hour and 30 minutes in the second. The star with the ball for Australia - Nathan Lyon. Credit has to be given to Pat Cummins as well as he was brilliant on a wicket which did not assist the pacers a lot.

Well, it has been a disastrous morning for England. They would have hoped to not lose more than a couple of wicket in the first session but have all their top 4 batsmen back in the hut. The onus will now be on the duo of Buttler and Stokes. The same pair who won them the World Cup will now have to fight it out in the longest form of the game if the hosts want to salvage this Test and avoid a defeat at the venue where they have enjoyed a lot of success. How will the second session pan out? Join us after the break to find out.

Lunch! No question who this session belonged to. Australia have dominated the morning session on Day 5. They wanted wickets in the first session and they have got 4 of them. It all hinged on how would Nathan Lyon do on this turning wicket and he has done remarkably. The GOAT has picked three wickets, including the big wicket of English skipper, Joe Root. Denly and Roy were his other victims. Lyon has been well supported by the trio of fast bowlers. In a pitch where there has been nothing for the seamers, Cummins, Siddle and Pattinson have bowled with determination and aggression not allowing England to get any easy runs. Cummins was the other one to get into the wickets column.

Outside off, Root defends it to point.
Length ball around off, Root defends it towards point and looks for a non-existent run and Buttler sensibly sends him back.
Buttler is off the mark! Length delivery on the body, Jos tucks it towards backward square leg and gets a single.
Good length ball on off, JR defends it towards cover and gets to the other end.
Fuller ball on off, Root defends it off the front foot.
Pat Cummins was given the ball but at the last minute the ball is given back to Siddle.

A brave leave! A good one in the end. Lyon bowls this flatter and outside off, Buttler covers his off pole and lets it be. Why brave? Because with the ball turning so much, you would not want to take that risk. End of another successful over for Lyon.
Jos Buttler is the new man in.

OUT! There is a clear edge! Not sure how he did not know that. England have lost one of their reviews. Lyon takes another. Denly's poor run with the bat continues and England in deep, deep trouble here. Lyon's ploy to come from around the wicket has worked. He floats it up on off, it pitches and turns back in. Denly looks to work it on the leg side but the ball hits the inside edge then the pad and lobs to Bancroft at short leg. Australia are celebrating and the umpire gives it out for caught. Denly walks upto his partner and reviews at the very end. Replays roll in and Ultra Edge shows a spike. Denly has to take the long walk back. Australia 7 wickets away now.
Denly reviews right at the end. He has been given out caught at short leg. Is there an edge? He would surely know.
Quicker and on off, Denly defends it nicely.
Lands on off and this is shorter. Root goes back and works it through square leg for one.
On middle and turning back in. Denly works it through square leg for one.
Fires it full and on the pads, Root plays the sweep towards deep square leg for one.
Good length delivery on off, Denly blocks it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Beauty of a delivery! On a good length and just outside off, Denly looks to defend but misses it due to the sharp inswinger on this one.
On a good length on off, Denly plays it to covers.
Good length delivery outside off, Denly lets it go.
Full again on middle, Denly plays it to mid-wicket.
Siddle bowls full on middle, Denly flicks it to short mid-wicket.
FOUR BYES! No chance for the keeper there. This is down the leg side, it spins away further. Root lets it be. Paine fails to collect it and it goes to the fine leg fence.
That stays low! Well played in the end! This is flatter and outside off, does not take off. Denly gets his bat down in time, works it through mid-wicket for one.
Loopy ball outside off, Denly once again plays the sweep but this time it hits the short leg fielder.
Plays the sweep shot and does so nicely but only for a run towards deep square leg.
Down the leg side, this is worked to short fine leg.
Flatter and on middle, Denly works it through square leg for one.
On a length and outside off, Root taps it to point.
Outside off, the skipper leaves it alone.
Bowls it down the leg side, Root looks to go after it but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Root blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Root keeps it out.
Full on middle, Root flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen pick up a couple.

FOUR! Another sweep shot! Denly may have realized that is one way to counter the big spin. He hits it well enough again, this time through mid-wicket for a boundary. End of an action-packed over. 9 and a wicket from it.
FOUR! Nicely played! Brings the sweep shot out, hits it really well through mid-wicket and bags a boundary.
Almost! This is lovely by Lyon. This is floated up outside off, it turns back in. Denly looks to defend but the ball hits the inside edge, then hits the pads and just about kisses the off pole.
Another appeal! This is on off and turns back in sharply. Denly looks to work it on the leg side but it clips the pads and goes to Paine who appeals but the umpire shakes his head.
Joe Denly is the new man in.

OUT! TIMBER! What was Roy doing there? He has literally thrown his wicket away. His patience runs out. He was playing so well, leaving the balls outside off, showing so much responsibility but eventually rush of blood has cost England here. Two down now 8 to go. Roy dances down the track as Lyon tosses it up outside off. Roy is nowhere near the pitch of the ball but still tries to go big. The ball turns back in. He misses and the stumps behind are disturbed.
Swept and done so nicely, towards deep square leg for one.
A single to end as Root works this one through square leg.
EDGY FOUR! This is just outside off, it is on a length. Root plays inside the line with soft hands. It goes off the outside edge down to third man for a boundary.
Back of a length on off, this is guided to point.
Outside off, the batter lets it be.
On off, blocked.
BEAUTY! This is just outside off, Root has a poke at it and gets beaten.
Flatter and outside off, this one turns back in. Roy at the very end, keeps it out.
Loopy ball on off, Roy defends it out.
Another good shot! This is very full and on off, Roy leans into it and strokes it through mid off for two.
FOUR! Excellent shot. Tossed up on middle, Roy sweeps it hard through square leg for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on middle, Root comes down the track and flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Floated delivery outside off, Root looks to sweep but misses it and gets hit low on the pads.
A beauty to end a top over! On off and it straightens again. Roy looks to push at it but gets beaten.
Too high! This is around middle and it jags back in. Roy looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads. An appeal but it is turned down.
Good length on off, Roy defends it.

EDGED AND FOUR! Paine was wrong footed there. Lucky escape for Roy. Siddle goes wide of the crease and angles it into the batter. Paine looking at the original trajectory, moves to his left. The ball pitches and straightens. Roy is squared up as he tries to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge past the diving Paine who does so to his right and to the third man fence. Paine was moving towards the left as the ball came towards him and hence, it was difficult to adjust.
On a good length and outside off, Roy shoulders his arms to this one.
Full on middle, Roy drives it to mid on.
DRINKS BREAK!
Another appeal but this is doing too much. This lands on middle and turns back in. Root looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but it is turned down.

Floats it up outside off, it turns back in. Root plays it with his bat behind the pad. It hits the pad. An appeal but the umpire shakes his head. He feels Root has played a shot there and Paine is not happy with that as he feels Root did not.
That spit off the surface! It pitches around off and turns back in and there is also extra bounce. Root does well to take one hand off the handle and work it on the leg side.
Flatter and shorter outside off, Root goes back and pushes it through covers for two.
Uses his feet but does not quite get to the pitch of the ball. He works it to mid on.
Shorter on off, this is worked with the turn to mid-wicket.
Nathan Lyon is on!
Fuller and on off, Root pushes it towards cover for one. Another eventful over comes to an end.
Outside off, left alone.

NOT OUT! There is an inside edge and a big one! The umpire is really not having a good day here. His second wrong decision today. This is on off and it jags back in. Root looks to defend but there are two sounds. One is surely of the ball hitting the pad. An appeal follows and the umpire raises the finger. Root reviews and Ultra Edge shows there is a big spike.
Root is given out LBW again! He reviews again. If no inside edge, it looks out.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Root looks to play inside the line of the delivery but misses it.
Good length delivery outside off, Root leaves it alone.
On a good length and outside off, Root shoulders his arms to this one.
Peter Siddle is on!
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
FOUR! Creamed! Fuller and on off, Roy leans into it and drives it crisply through covers. Bags another boundary.
The batsman defends it from within the crease. They pick up a single.
Back of a length on middle, Root defends it late. He almost ends up chopping it onto the stumps. He though was aware to hit as he was ready to push it away with the bat.
NO BALL! Cummins oversteps. A bumper on middle, Root ducks under it.
Back of a length on off, Root stands tall and keeps it out.
On a good length on middle, Root defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Roy keeps it out.
Bowls a bouncer outside leg, Roy does well to duck under it. Tim Paine dives to his left to collect it.
Roy once again complains about some noise coming from the stumps area. The umpires have called the ground staff out. A change of stumps maybe? Yes, the middle stump has been changed.
On off, Roy defends it to mid off.
There is some issue with the stumps here. The umpire is having a look. Not sure what the exact issue is. It has been solved and we are all set to continue.
FOUR! Just a push there by Roy! Pattinson goes fuller and around off, Roy leans into it and strokes it through covers. Mid off gives it a chase but he has no chance.
On the stumps, Roy defends it towards mid on.
Good length and outside off, Roy lets it be.
FOUR! A little too full this time and Root bags a boundary. On off, Root strokes it with the full face of the bat past mid off. Mid on gives it a chase but finishes second best.
Just outside off, Root once again looks to play at it at first but then bails out.
Works it with the angle down to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Outside off, Roy covers his off pole and leaves it.
Cuts him into half there! This is outside off and on a length. It comes back in. Roy pushes outside the line and misses. The ball goes close past the off pole.
On a good length on off, Roy defends it off the front foot.

NOT OUT! Going down leg! A successful review by Root. England will breathe a sigh of relief as this would have been a body blow for England. Pattinson angles this into the pads. Root looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards the leg side as the batters run a leg bye. In the meantime, the bowler is appealing. The umpire raises his finger. Root reviews immediately. Replays roll in and they show the on-field call has to be overturned. Also, the run will be cancelled as the umpire had given Root out.
Big moment in the game! Root has been given out LBW. He reviews. This could be a good review.
FOUR! Too short and too easy for Root. He gets off the mark with a boundary. Shorter and around off, Joe stands tall and punches it through covers. No stopping that.
Way too wide outside off, Root lets it be.

Was there an edge? Paine did feel so. Warner had a 'not very sure' look on his face. This is shorter and outside off, Root looks to punch it through the off side but misses. The ball goes low and to the right of Paine who takes and appeals. He is the only one doing so. The umpire is not interested. He does not review. Ultra Edge does show a small spike but not sure what was that off.
Once again a good stop! Lyon it is! Shorter and around off, Root guides it towards point where Nathan dives to his left and saves two at least.
Even the fielders are backing up the bowlers! A good stop by the fielder. This is on the pads, Root works it towards mid-wicket. The fielder dives to his left and stops it.
Pattinson is giving him good support. He oversteps this time but still. He lands it outside off and on a length. Root makes a leave.

That is a rippa! Lethal stuff from Cummins. Once again goes wide of the crease and lands it on off, gets it to straighten. Roy is beaten all ends up as he tries to defend. Cummins is amidst a brilliant spell here. Exactly what we are use to seeing from him and something we missed in the first innings.
Cummins looks up for it today! He bowls a sharp bumper now which Roy ducks under it.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls it just outside off, left alone.
Another good ball! This lands outside off and straightens. Roy keeps it out.
Another one on a length and around off, it is defended.
Just behind a driving length outside off, Roy lets it be. A cautious approach maybe by the opener or he tends to go hard at such deliveries.
Slightly fuller and around off, Root defends it out.
Back of a length and on off, Root defends it onto the ground.
OHHH! Outside off, Root initially looks to play at it but then realizes he need not so lets it be.
A little too straight, Roy works it through mid-wicket and a single taken.
Back of a length and on off, Roy stands tall and defends it out.
A good short one by Pattinson this time. It is on the body, Roy moves out of the way.
Goes shorter again, not the same zip on it as the last ball. Root blocks it out.
Joe Root is the new batsman in.

OUT! In the air... taken! 1 down, 9 to go! Cummins bowls an absolute brute of a delivery to get the centurion of the first innings. It is shorter in length and Cummins bends his back on this one. Skids through and also gets big on the batter. Burns does not have enough time to move out of the way so he looks to fend at it. The ball hits the higher portion of the bat and lobs towards point where Lyon takes a dolly. Early wicket for Australia, ideal start for them.
On the fuller side again on middle, Burns strokes it back to the bowler.
Around off and on a fuller length, Rory pushes it towards covers.
Bowls it outside off, Burns lets it be.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the batter, Roy looks to defend but it goes off the inner half wide of mid on for one.
Down the leg side, the batter looks to flick but misses.
Back of a length on middle, blocked.

A loud shout but nothing from the umpire! This is angled into the pads. Roy looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but it is going down leg. The ball rolls towards the leg side and a leg bye is taken. No signal from the umpire so there might be a faint edge. Ultra Edge confirms that.
Goes fuller this time and on middle, Roy shows the full face of the bat and strokes it to mid on.
Closer to the off pole this time but not close enough to make the batter play.
A loosener to begin! Full and wide outside off, Roy lets it be.
James Pattinson to bowl from the other end.
Another one outside off, Burns lets it be. A good comeback by Cummins after going for a boundary on the first ball.
This lands on middle and then angles away. Burns goes back and keeps it out.
Another delivery which is outside the off pole, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
This one is bowled outside off, Burns lets it be.

A beauty! Excellent comeback! He drags his length back a little and lands it on off, it goes away with the angle. Burns looks to defend but does so inside the line. The ball whizzes past the outside edge.
FOUR! That is a confident start by Burns. A lovely defensive push for a boundary. On a length and around off, Burns pushes it through extra cover and the ball races away to the fence.

We are all set to begin Day 5. It is bright and sunny at the moment which is probably good for England. Their batters, Jason Roy and Rory Burns, will resume their innings. The Australian players are out in a huddle. They seemed quite relax. The visitors now make their way to the middle. Pat Cummins, who did not bowl an over yesterday, will start the proceedings for Australia. Three slips and a gully in place. Here we go...

The equation is simple today, Australia need 10 wickets to take a 1-0 lead whereas England have to score 385 in around 90 overs if they are to win the first Test. The latter part looks improbable so one would assume, the hosts would look to play out for a draw. The wicket yesterday was on the slower side but being the 5th day, there might just be more wear and tear and more assistance to the bowlers. It is not going to be easy for the home side. The first session, actually, the first hour is the important one. If England play that out without much damage, they would back themselves to save this game. An exciting day of cricket waits ahead. Welcome to the coverage.
... Day 5, Session 1 ...

England on the other hand, will probably first try and save this game! They need another 385 runs but scoring that in one day, is quite impossible. The hosts need to go session by session, analyze their position and then see how they need to go about things. They have a batting line-up capable of surviving a whole day but will they be able to do so? We will find out on Day 5 as all the action begins at 1100 local (1000 GMT). Till then, take care and goodbye!

Australia can be very pleased with where they are in the game at the moment! However, one could argue they could have declared a lot earlier. Hindsight is always a good thing. They still are favorites to win this game after tons from Smith and Wade. They have around 90 overs on Monday to take the 10 England wickets and by the look of things, the wicket is assisting the spinner so probably, Nathan Lyon will be the key for them.

England will enter Day 5, without any damage being done! Their openers have survived the nervy period. There were many oohs and aahs but they will be happy with the fact that they have not lost a wicket. They though are still way behind in the game.

Almost does produce some magic on the last ball! A beauty to start the over, a jaffa to finish. Still though, one would feel, he was pretty short in the last over. The last ball though was bowled just behind a driving length outside off, Roy initially looks to push at it, does so tentatively but luckily for him, he gets beaten. He survives. THAT IS STUMPS ON DAY 4!
Too short again! Easy for Roy. He goes back and keeps it out. One ball to negotiate for Jason.
Once again on the shorter side, Roy works it through square leg and takes an easy two.
A bit short again, Roy stands tall and keeps it out. Pattinson needs to be a little fuller here. Three balls to go before Stumps.
Goes short and on the body, Roy looks to play it cautiously but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
That is a gem! Can't do a lot about it. This is angled into the off pole, pitches and moves away. Roy plays the original trajectory but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
The straighter one to end. It is on middle, Burns defends it out.

That is a beauty! Just unplayable! This pitches on middle and then turns square. Burns does nothing wrong as he tries to defend but due to the spin, the ball almost kisses the outside edge and the off pole.
Extremely full, the spin is out of contention there. Roy jams it out towards covers for one.
Quicker and fuller outside off, a waste of a delivery. Roy lets it be.
Gives it air and bowls it slightly fuller outside off, Roy defends it out.
Flatter and on off, this one turns back in. Roy goes back and keeps it out.
On the pads of Burns, he flicks it towards square leg.
Again length ball on off, Burns plays this one towards mid off.
This time shorter in length, Burns defends it off the back foot towards mid off.
Solid front foot defense offered by Burns. Pattinson bowls it full on middle and off, Rory gets on the front foot and defends it back to the bowler.
On the hips of Burns, he tucks it towards square leg.
Outside off to start off by Pattinson. Burns lets it go.
James Pattinson is into the attack.

Brilliantly bowled again! Slows it up one more time and floats it wider outside off. He wants Roy to go after it. Roy does so with hard hands. The ball turns back in and it goes off the inner half to mid-wicket. A good over this by Lyon.
Lovely! Excellent! Gives it flight and lands it around off, Roy lunges and tries to defend but due to the turn back in, it goes off the inner half to mid-wicket.
Very short this time, Roy has enough time to go back and push it through covers for two.
Not the right shot that. This is shorter and outside off, Roy goes back and looks to cut but the ball skids through and beats the bat.
That was good! Fuller than the last one. Roy goes back to a ball he should play forward to. It stays low. Roy though does well to get his bat down in time.
Flatter and outside off, Roy goes back and pushes it to covers. Once again Lyon is a little too short.
Again outside off but the ball nips back in this time. Burns again leaves it as he exactly knows where his stumps are.
Outside off on a length, Burns shoulders arms to it.
Fuller this time, just outside the off pole, it takes the leading edge of Burns' bat and goes towards the 4th slip fielder as he dives to his left and stops it.
Length ball outside off, it shapes away after pitching. Burns shoulders arms to it.
Short of a length ball on off, Burns blocks it out to the off side.
Full ball on the off pole, Burns pushes it through long on. The fielders give it a chase and cut it off as the batters take two.
Gives it a lot of air and lands it on off, Roy leans forward and keeps it out. Lyon was a little too short in his first over. Needs to get it right quickly, not a lot of overs to be bowled today.
Flatter and shorter again, Roy goes back and works it to short leg.
Well bowled! He floats it up outside off, the ball pitches and then turns back in. Roy lunges and keeps it out.
Flatter and on middle, it is shorter in length. Burns works it through mid-wicket and takes three.
Flatter and on middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Flatter but down the leg side. Roy lets it be.
Length ball outside off, Burns shoulders arms to it.
Again on the hips of Burns, he tucks it towards mid-wicket.
On the pads of Burns, he has flicked this one onto the leg side.
Goes back to bowling length and on off, Burns defends it onto the ground.
England are underway! A fuller ball around off, Burns strokes it through covers and the batsmen take two.
On a good length and outside off, Burns lets it be.
